I enjoyed this. The idea of these whales repairing the environment just by existing is a really nice starting hook, and the detail you go into with how exactly they're doing it adds a good sense of verisimilitude to the article. World-building is always something I appreciate in articles, too, and the mention of the Parazoology Division scratches that itch nicely.

The ending, with it being implied that the Foundation are going to take steps to preserve the species to repair the Earth - normalcy be damned - is a really nice way to leave it off, too. If I had to say something that didn't quite work for me, it'd be the discovery log - it's really nicely put together, with the communications between the ship and the base, but I don't know how much it really adds to the article.

Still, there's a hearty +1 here from me!

